==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whitebait
<hw>White"bait`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The young of several species of herrings, especially
of the common herring, esteemed a great delicacy by epicures in
England.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A small translucent fish (<spn>Salanx
Chinensis</spn>) abundant at certain seasons on the coasts of China and
Japan, and used in the same manner as the European whitebait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

